title: Franchise value of the San Francisco Giants 2002 to 2019
yAxis: Franchise value in million U.S. dollars
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, containing a total of 18 data points.
Overall Franchise value in million U.S. dollars has increased over the Year.
Franchise value in million U.S. dollars is roughly constant from 2002 to 2010, gradually increasing from 2010 to 2016, and lastly roughly constant from 2016 to 2019.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2014 and 2015.
Maximum Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, about 3000.0 was reported at Year 2019
The lowest Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, of value 355.0 was reported at Year 2002
